.TH "devm_fwnode_gpiod_get_index" 9 "devm_fwnode_gpiod_get_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_fwnode_gpiod_get_index \- get a GPIO descriptor from a given node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gpio_desc *" devm_fwnode_gpiod_get_index
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct fwnode_handle *fwnode "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "enum gpiod_flags flags "  ","
.BI "const char *label "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
GPIO consumer
.IP "fwnode" 12
firmware node containing GPIO reference
.IP "con_id" 12
function within the GPIO consumer
.IP "index" 12
index of the GPIO to obtain in the consumer
.IP "flags" 12
GPIO initialization flags
.IP "label" 12
label to attach to the requested GPIO
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
GPIO descriptors returned from this function are automatically disposed on
driver detach.

On successful request the GPIO pin is configured in accordance with
provided \fIflags\fP.
